<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-20T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-20T03:00:00-05:00" n="1098" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1098">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">811.503193/8–2047: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Meyer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-20T17:00:00+09:00">August 20,
                                1947—5 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received August 20—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2029. Present tentative plan of Chinese Government for disposition of textile
                        mills of China Textile Industries Incorporated calls for outright sale of
                        70% of the number of mills to private investors and Government to retain
                        ownership of remaining mills for production of military cotton textile
                        supplies.</p>
                    <p>Details of plan for disposition of plants not yet decided upon. <pb facs="1390" n="1380" xml:id="pg_1380"/> ReDeptel 1230, July 25.
                        Consulate General forwarding by despatch<note n="27" xml:id="d1098fn1">Despatch No. 1624, August 30, not printed.</note> preliminary estimate
                        of evaluation of 17 Shanghai mills.</p>
                    <p>Sent Department, repeated Nanking 1458.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Meyer</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>